WEBVTT

00:00.033 --> 00:01.062
<i>Previously on</i> "Suits"

00:01.065 --> 00:02.352
I'm talking about
the both of us,

00:02.400 --> 00:04.664
convincing hardman that two
kickass junior partners

00:04.813 --> 00:07.468
are worth as much as one new
senior partner.

00:07.523 --> 00:09.673
You had the chance to triple
our business,

00:09.721 --> 00:11.470
and all you had to do was
take a knee.

00:11.518 --> 00:13.103
Tell me right now you weren't
the one

00:13.127 --> 00:14.611
that Fletcher engines
my game plan.

00:14.659 --> 00:16.479
Hardman told me he wasn't
gonna make you partner anyway.

00:16.526 --> 00:18.283
And once he offered it to me,
all I had to do was...

00:18.330 --> 00:19.352
Sell me out.

00:19.400 --> 00:21.205
Mike's pro bono
is against some prison.

00:21.253 --> 00:22.470
And guess who builds
those prisons.

00:22.518 --> 00:23.533
I gave him my word.

00:23.581 --> 00:24.838
And you once gave your word
to me

00:24.886 --> 00:25.931
and went back on it.

00:25.979 --> 00:28.196
I had to lie to Harvey's face.

00:28.244 --> 00:29.376
You either go and work
at the clinic

00:29.423 --> 00:30.902
or you stay at Pearson Specter.

00:30.950 --> 00:32.418
But you can't play them both
for fools

00:32.465 --> 00:33.856
and put me in the middle.

00:33.904 --> 00:35.942
I have a binding agreement
signed by his legal clinic,

00:35.989 --> 00:37.232
stating that they would have
no outside help

00:37.279 --> 00:38.932
from Pearson Specter litt
on this case.

00:39.004 --> 00:40.440
- Yet they did.
- You convinced me

00:40.488 --> 00:41.457
the only way to heal

00:41.505 --> 00:43.449
was to keep this from happening
to someone else,

00:43.497 --> 00:45.340
and now I have nothing.

00:45.388 --> 00:46.902
This isn't just about you
protecting

00:46.950 --> 00:48.160
your client's interests.

00:48.208 --> 00:49.769
It's about you protecting
yourself.

00:49.831 --> 00:52.441
Why don't you tell me
what's really going on here?

00:56.581 --> 00:57.824
That's it.

00:58.118 --> 01:00.277
They've had me
by the balls ever since.

01:00.331 --> 01:03.074
Jesus... how'd you let yourself
get compromised like that?

01:03.144 --> 01:04.589
This is my situation, Harvey.

01:04.667 --> 01:06.744
- No.
- This is a firm situation,

01:06.792 --> 01:09.379
and we need to cut ties with those
bastards right the hell now.

01:09.427 --> 01:11.029
- I don't believe this.
- You're pulling

01:11.077 --> 01:12.920
rank after I opened up to you?
That's bullshit.

01:12.968 --> 01:14.035
No, Alex.

01:14.083 --> 01:15.924
What's bullshit is
you letting yourself

01:15.972 --> 01:18.371
be put in that position
for the last five years.

01:18.419 --> 01:19.841
- Letting?
- Yeah, letting.

01:19.889 --> 01:22.579
And now I gotta get us out,
because you did this to me.

01:22.627 --> 01:24.436
Well, as long as we're
throwing blame around, Harvey,

01:24.483 --> 01:25.919
I didn't do shit to you.

01:26.348 --> 01:27.739
You did this to me.

01:27.814 --> 01:30.147
♪♪ <i>Tense music...</i>

01:30.194 --> 01:31.646
♪♪

01:31.735 --> 01:33.513
All in.

01:33.971 --> 01:35.505
Not this time, brother.

01:35.639 --> 01:36.705
I got you.

01:36.841 --> 01:38.255
Bullshit, you got me.

01:38.364 --> 01:39.763
Uh-huh.
I know how you play.

01:39.867 --> 01:41.982
You checked to open.
You got jack/ten at best.

01:42.068 --> 01:44.450
This is a bluff.
I'm calling.

01:44.607 --> 01:46.263
Do what you have to do.

01:49.525 --> 01:51.443
Kings over sevens,
motherfu... er.

01:52.044 --> 01:53.552
Trip sevens, little man.

01:53.615 --> 01:56.341
Maybe you don't know
how I play after all.

01:56.453 --> 01:58.320
Uh-uh.
You're on tilt.

01:58.342 --> 01:59.542
You've been on tilt all night.

01:59.590 --> 02:01.193
That was a stupid play
and you know it.

02:01.254 --> 02:02.943
What's going on with you?

02:06.427 --> 02:07.871
I was supposed to
make partner today,

02:07.919 --> 02:10.687
but Louis litt screwed me over,
so there.

02:10.735 --> 02:11.884
That's why I'm pissed.

02:11.976 --> 02:13.169
Shit.

02:13.371 --> 02:14.470
I didn't know.

02:14.543 --> 02:16.143
Well, now you do.

02:16.411 --> 02:17.590
I don't understand, Harvey.

02:17.638 --> 02:19.147
I thought you were Jessica
Pearson's guy over there.

02:19.194 --> 02:21.364
I thought so too,
but she didn't have my back.

02:22.907 --> 02:24.443
Well, what if I had your back?

02:24.491 --> 02:25.607
What are you talking about?

02:25.655 --> 02:26.966
I heard
Tommy Bratton talking.

02:27.014 --> 02:28.482
They're looking to
bring someone in.

02:28.591 --> 02:30.652
You say the word,
I bet I can get you in as partner.

02:30.700 --> 02:31.731
What's in it for you?

02:31.779 --> 02:33.243
Bratton's about to
make an offer

02:33.291 --> 02:34.801
to some big-time earner
at skadden.

02:34.849 --> 02:36.388
I say you and me go in there

02:36.436 --> 02:39.098
and tell him two junior partners
are a hell of a lot better

02:39.146 --> 02:40.191
than one senior partner.

02:40.239 --> 02:41.302
- Pass.
- Come on, Harvey.

02:41.365 --> 02:42.622
At least think about it.

02:42.671 --> 02:43.811
I don't need
to think about it.

02:43.858 --> 02:45.427
I just went through
the same thing,

02:45.475 --> 02:46.708
and the guy who proposed it

02:46.756 --> 02:48.239
ended up stabbing me
in the back.

02:48.310 --> 02:49.505
I wouldn't do that to you.

02:49.553 --> 02:51.747
Yeah, well,
I appreciate your offer, but...

02:52.130 --> 02:53.786
I'm not going to give you
the opportunity.

02:54.419 --> 02:57.684
Now, you need me to stake you?

02:58.005 --> 02:59.552
There's 300.

02:59.677 --> 03:03.372
♪♪

03:11.036 --> 03:12.302
- Hey.
- Hey.

03:12.372 --> 03:13.749
I heard about
what happened in court.

03:13.796 --> 03:15.677
I know you gave up the case,
Mike, I'm sorry.

03:15.762 --> 03:17.731
Rachel, I gave the case up
because you reminded me

03:17.802 --> 03:19.848
to be a man of my word,
but like I said,

03:19.966 --> 03:22.106
I gave my word
to Oscar Reyes first.

03:22.528 --> 03:23.577
What does that mean?

03:23.625 --> 03:25.239
It means that
I don't want to lie to you,

03:25.287 --> 03:28.145
and I don't want to lie
to Harvey, but...

03:28.848 --> 03:30.966
I'm going to get this case
opened in criminal court,

03:31.098 --> 03:32.761
and for the record,
that does not violate

03:32.809 --> 03:33.987
the agreement that I signed.

03:34.044 --> 03:36.222
So you're going to
tell Harvey, right?

03:36.270 --> 03:37.761
If he asks me,
I'll tell him,

03:37.809 --> 03:38.993
but I'm not going to
volunteer it,

03:39.040 --> 03:40.348
and I need to know
if you're good with that.

03:40.395 --> 03:41.549
- Mike...
- Before you answer,

03:41.596 --> 03:43.153
I want you
to think about the fact

03:43.265 --> 03:45.419
that these guys are
extending sentences.

03:45.533 --> 03:47.864
♪♪

03:48.098 --> 03:50.355
What if it were me in there,
and it was my sentence

03:50.403 --> 03:51.668
that got extended?

03:51.716 --> 03:53.450
I just have one question.

03:53.980 --> 03:55.919
What if
Harvey asks me about it?

03:56.012 --> 03:57.473
Then you tell him the truth.

03:57.531 --> 03:59.297
♪♪

03:59.364 --> 04:02.184
Then yeah,
I'm good with it.

04:02.298 --> 04:05.020
♪♪

04:05.586 --> 04:09.083
<i>♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪</i>

04:09.137 --> 04:12.446
<i>♪ Get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪</i>

04:12.552 --> 04:15.661
<i>♪ Everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪</i>

04:15.770 --> 04:19.144
<i>♪ Everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪</i>

04:19.209 --> 04:22.341
<i>♪ I'll even eat a bean pie,
I don't mind ♪</i>

04:22.427 --> 04:26.216
<i>♪ Me and Missy is so busy,
busy making money ♪</i>

04:26.286 --> 04:27.575
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

04:27.630 --> 04:33.348
<i>♪ All step back, I'm 'bout to dance ♪
