04:33.432 --> 04:35.239
<i>♪ The greenback boogie ♪</i>

04:35.774 --> 04:38.441
♪♪ <i> Solemn music...</i>

04:38.514 --> 04:42.186
♪♪

04:46.733 --> 04:47.886
What's this?

04:47.934 --> 04:50.100
I never thanked you
for allowing me into the bar,

04:50.148 --> 04:52.569
and I figured you'd prefer a
criminal case to a fruit basket.

04:52.622 --> 04:53.688
This is a civil case.

04:53.736 --> 04:55.622
It was
a civil case.

04:55.739 --> 04:57.056
But it doesn't have to be.

04:57.160 --> 04:59.005
That doesn't sound like
a gift to me.

04:59.053 --> 05:00.329
It sounds like a favor for you.

05:00.377 --> 05:02.284
Anita, you said you're about
doing what's right.

05:02.332 --> 05:04.536
People are being kept
in prison for money.

05:04.747 --> 05:05.800
That's not right.

05:05.848 --> 05:06.848
If that's true.

05:06.896 --> 05:08.756
I wish there was something I
could do about it, but I can't.

05:08.803 --> 05:09.864
What do you mean,
you can't?

05:09.911 --> 05:10.989
You know what I mean.

05:11.037 --> 05:12.934
Nobody wants to see me
spending my time

05:12.982 --> 05:14.826
getting bad guys
<i>out</i> of prison.

05:14.934 --> 05:17.222
And what if I told you
it was a criminal conspiracy

05:17.270 --> 05:18.989
between two fortune 500
companies?

05:19.059 --> 05:20.372
What are you talking about?

05:20.453 --> 05:22.410
I couldn't pursue the case
because we represent

05:22.458 --> 05:24.684
another client who was
pressuring me to drop it,

05:24.747 --> 05:26.261
and there's no way
they did that

05:26.309 --> 05:28.630
just to protect reform corp.,
which means they're in on it.

05:28.738 --> 05:29.893
Do you have any proof?

05:29.941 --> 05:31.027
No, but...

05:31.075 --> 05:34.019
you bring me some proof of
a conspiracy and I'll pursue it.

05:34.067 --> 05:35.137
That's the best I can do.

05:35.185 --> 05:36.716
Anita, I don't have
the resources to...

05:36.764 --> 05:38.036
not my problem.

05:38.175 --> 05:41.458
♪♪

05:41.505 --> 05:43.505
♪♪

05:43.780 --> 05:44.913
And another thing...

05:45.028 --> 05:46.583
♪ ♪

05:46.653 --> 05:48.089
whatever you do bring me

05:48.137 --> 05:49.941
has to be
on the reform corp. Side

05:49.989 --> 05:51.310
of the arrangement,
because if it isn't,

05:51.357 --> 05:53.418
you're breaking privilege,
and I can't use any of it.

05:53.465 --> 05:57.075
♪♪

05:57.122 --> 06:00.864
♪♪

06:02.617 --> 06:04.325
Harvey.

06:04.989 --> 06:07.222
There's something I want to tell
you, but I need to know

06:07.270 --> 06:09.286
if you're over what happened
with Louis and the promotion.

06:09.333 --> 06:10.705
I'm fine, Donna.

06:10.833 --> 06:14.067
Good, because I need to leave
work early tomorrow night.

06:14.191 --> 06:15.255
What for?

06:15.347 --> 06:17.680
It's my six-month anniversary
with Mark.

06:18.403 --> 06:20.145
- What's that face?
- Nothing.

06:20.195 --> 06:22.550
I guess I just didn't think
you were one of those people.

06:22.598 --> 06:24.512
- What people?
- The people that celebrate

06:24.560 --> 06:26.467
their niece's
third-grade graduation

06:26.515 --> 06:27.631
like it was
the moon landing.

06:27.678 --> 06:30.403
And when was the last time you saw
anyone seriously for six months?

06:30.451 --> 06:32.300
I'm not the topic
of this conversation.

06:32.348 --> 06:33.371
How could you be?

06:33.419 --> 06:34.511
Because we're talking about

06:34.559 --> 06:36.677
a mature and committed
relationship.

06:36.778 --> 06:38.083
You're right, Donna, we are,

06:38.131 --> 06:43.497
which is why... I got you a gift
to celebrate your anniversary.

06:49.786 --> 06:51.309
Harvey...

06:52.348 --> 06:54.742
This is very generous,
but I can't accept it.

06:54.802 --> 06:56.208
- Why not?
- Because mark

06:56.278 --> 06:57.773
planned a special night for us,

06:57.821 --> 06:59.645
and how's he going to feel
when I pull out a gift card

06:59.692 --> 07:00.668
to help pay for it?

07:00.716 --> 07:02.293
- That wasn't the idea.
- I know,

07:02.341 --> 07:04.144
but if you want to
really give me a gift,

07:04.192 --> 07:07.145
promise you won't call or
interrupt me the entire night.

07:07.286 --> 07:08.323
I promise.

07:08.380 --> 07:09.397
Thanks, Harvey.

07:09.473 --> 07:11.266
♪♪

07:11.372 --> 07:13.488
God damn it, Jeffrey,
this is a place of business,

07:13.536 --> 07:16.325
not a petting zoo, so you
either flush the goldfish or you're fired.

07:16.373 --> 07:18.052
You don't have the authority
to do that.

07:18.145 --> 07:20.520
Section 207,
paragraph three of the by-laws:

07:20.583 --> 07:23.433
Insubordination to a partner
results in termination.

07:23.481 --> 07:25.372
This has nothing to do with
my fish and you know it.

07:25.419 --> 07:26.882
It's got everything to do
with that fish,

07:26.929 --> 07:28.256
and I don't want to hear
another word about it,

07:28.303 --> 07:29.326
so unless you want to
say another word...

07:29.373 --> 07:31.481
Louis,
can I talk to you for a second?

07:31.529 --> 07:32.678
Hey, Jessica, I was just
in the middle of something...

07:32.725 --> 07:33.858
now.

07:37.833 --> 07:38.847
Yes?

07:38.895 --> 07:39.880
What the hell
do you think you're doing?

07:39.928 --> 07:41.231
I'm exercising my authority

07:41.279 --> 07:43.122
as junior partner
over that douche.

07:43.208 --> 07:44.348
By trying to kill his fish?

07:44.396 --> 07:45.754
No, by trying to keep order
in the bullpen.

07:45.801 --> 07:47.246
Jessica,
Jeffrey's work habits are...

07:47.294 --> 07:48.967
it's because I didn't
call him junior partner.

07:49.014 --> 07:51.021
Shut up, this has nothing
to do with how I feel about

07:51.068 --> 07:53.068
his stupid, disrespectful
asshole fish.

07:53.411 --> 07:54.677
Louis...

07:55.560 --> 07:56.974
Have you considered
therapy?

07:57.022 --> 07:58.161
Why would I do that?

07:58.209 --> 08:00.067
That would be like baryshnikov
taking dance lessons.

08:00.114 --> 08:01.151
- Louis...
- Jessica,

08:01.199 --> 08:02.262
shrinks are for pussies.

08:02.310 --> 08:03.918
Now, can I go back to
yelling at Jeffrey?

08:04.037 --> 08:05.903
Because these associates need
guidance and discipline.

08:05.950 --> 08:06.972
Listen to me, Louis.

08:07.020 --> 08:08.895
I stayed out of that whole
thing between you and Harvey

08:08.942 --> 08:10.394
because that was Daniel's call.

08:10.418 --> 08:12.456
And you want to go off on the
associates, that's one thing,

08:12.503 --> 08:14.113
but you let this promotion go
to your head,

08:14.160 --> 08:15.777
and you take it out on Harvey,

08:16.175 --> 08:18.081
I'm going to step the hell
back in.

08:18.808 --> 08:20.581
Jessica, you have my word
as junior partner:

08:20.629 --> 08:21.707
If there's any problem
with Harvey,

08:21.754 --> 08:22.972
it won't be because of me.

08:23.159 --> 08:26.847
♪♪

08:30.213 --> 08:31.400
I'm a little busy right now.

08:31.448 --> 08:33.111
Well, whatever it is,
put it to the side.

08:33.181 --> 08:34.621
Daniel wants you to work
with Louis

08:34.669 --> 08:36.486
on the reinsdorf case.

08:36.745 --> 08:39.010
You got something to say,
Harvey, say it.

08:39.256 --> 08:40.548
Okay, I'll say it.

08:40.643 --> 08:43.043
You didn't have my back
when hardman screwed me over,

08:43.091 --> 08:44.392
and now
you're carrying his water

08:44.440 --> 08:45.641
while he tries to humiliate me.

08:45.688 --> 08:47.243
I don't care what he's doing.

08:47.291 --> 08:49.571
I care about what I'm doing,
which is to see if you can

08:49.628 --> 08:52.556
put that ego of yours aside
and play the long game.

08:52.604 --> 08:53.893
What the hell
are you talking about?

08:53.940 --> 08:56.595
Do you have any idea
how many times I had to smile

08:56.643 --> 08:59.814
and take it when Charles Van
dyke pawned his work off on me?

08:59.987 --> 09:02.087
Or when Stanley Gordon would
call me into his office

09:02.135 --> 09:03.834
just so he could ogle my ass
when I left?

09:03.882 --> 09:04.915
That is not the same thing.

09:04.962 --> 09:07.096
Not to mention when schmidt
would talk about "the blacks"

09:07.143 --> 09:09.431
like he was living in 1950.

09:10.079 --> 09:12.431
I sucked it up for years,
Harvey.

09:13.153 --> 09:14.400
Now it's your turn.

09:14.470 --> 09:15.595
What if I won't?

09:15.643 --> 09:17.487
Then you're not my guy,
because if you can't even

09:17.534 --> 09:19.361
pretend to bend a knee
to your rivals,

09:19.432 --> 09:21.992
it doesn't matter what you do to
get ahead of them in the future.

09:22.410 --> 09:25.087
They're going to see you coming
a mile away.

09:25.670 --> 09:29.384
♪♪

09:29.431 --> 09:32.743
♪♪

09:32.874 --> 09:34.704
Mr. kreuger,
I appreciate you meeting me.

09:34.752 --> 09:36.062
This isn't downton Abbey,
Harvey.

09:36.110 --> 09:37.540
It's a construction firm.

09:37.650 --> 09:39.337
Call me pat,
or see yourself out.

09:39.385 --> 09:40.423
Fair enough, pat.

09:40.471 --> 09:42.548
I'm sure you know that
a junior partner at our firm

09:42.596 --> 09:44.296
broke his word.

09:44.707 --> 09:46.673
I think you're owed an apology.

09:51.352 --> 09:53.220
Usually the clients pay
the lawyers,

09:53.268 --> 09:54.368
not the other way around.

09:54.416 --> 09:56.087
This is a unique situation.

09:56.135 --> 09:57.869
This looks a lot like
you're trying to pay me off.

09:57.916 --> 10:01.184
I'm trying to make things right,
and allow you to move on.

10:02.136 --> 10:05.150
You want to know how to get
someone's best effort, Harvey?

10:05.293 --> 10:06.892
It's not paying them
the most money.

10:06.965 --> 10:08.498
It's making sure that
their interests

10:08.546 --> 10:10.134
are aligned with yours,

10:10.326 --> 10:13.261
and Alex Williams wants this
case to go away as much as I do.

10:13.309 --> 10:15.345
You don't need your interests
aligned anymore.

10:15.393 --> 10:16.587
This case is over.

10:16.635 --> 10:18.884
Maybe it is.
And maybe it isn't.

10:19.016 --> 10:21.650
But I've heard that
from your firm once before.

10:21.892 --> 10:24.767
And then I believe
it was your own associate

10:24.919 --> 10:27.056
who opened the case again
in the first place.

10:27.199 --> 10:29.665
So, you see, Harvey,
it's not just Alex's interests

10:29.713 --> 10:32.431
that are aligned with mine.
It's yours.

10:32.720 --> 10:35.236
And I plan to keep it that way.

10:35.587 --> 10:39.243
♪♪

10:39.290 --> 10:42.564
♪♪

10:43.103 --> 10:46.728
♪♪

10:46.775 --> 10:50.470
♪♪

10:54.252 --> 10:56.853
Let me guess: You're here to
go over my testimony.

10:57.028 --> 10:58.930
I already told you
I'm not giving you anything

10:58.978 --> 11:00.150
until my daughter gets paid.

11:00.198 --> 11:01.362
It's not what I'm here for,
Frank.

11:01.409 --> 11:04.712
I need to know if you know anything
about a conspiracy outside of reform corp.

11:04.895 --> 11:06.923
Conspiracy outside of r...

11:07.296 --> 11:08.395
What are you talking about?

11:08.443 --> 11:10.454
What the hell's going on here?

11:11.017 --> 11:12.268
We got thrown off the case.

11:12.316 --> 11:13.368
What did you just say to me?

11:13.415 --> 11:15.071
- Frank...
- 'cause you came in here

11:15.119 --> 11:16.501
promising my daughter
a future.

11:16.549 --> 11:18.284
Now you're telling me
it's all a bunch of shit.

11:18.331 --> 11:19.562
It's not a bunch of shit,

11:19.610 --> 11:20.869
and I can get the case reopened,

11:20.916 --> 11:22.469
but I need evidence
of a conspiracy

11:22.517 --> 11:23.620
with Masterson construction.

11:23.667 --> 11:26.142
Then I can't help you,
'cause all I know is,

11:26.275 --> 11:28.244
those are the guys
that put us all to work.

11:28.292 --> 11:29.425
Work?

11:29.554 --> 11:30.697
What are you talking about?

11:30.745 --> 11:32.509
Those places
aren't like danbury.

11:32.590 --> 11:34.590
We work our asses off
to build their prison

11:34.638 --> 11:36.494
so they can put more of us away.

11:36.728 --> 11:39.306
But if you're looking for
a conspiracy, there's not.

11:39.354 --> 11:42.392
They do it all out in the open,
call it "rehabilitation."

11:42.463 --> 11:45.205
Well, it may not have been
hidden, but something is.

11:45.386 --> 11:48.111
And I think you just pointed me
in the right direction.

11:48.242 --> 11:50.111
♪♪

11:50.276 --> 11:52.362
- What the hell did you do?
- What are you talking about?

11:52.409 --> 11:54.033
You went to Masterson
behind my back.

11:54.081 --> 11:55.714
I did what I told you
I was going to do.

11:55.762 --> 11:57.676
I got you into this mess,
I'm going to get you out.

11:57.723 --> 11:58.786
Then all
going to Masterson does

11:58.833 --> 12:00.036
is put you
in their crosshairs.

12:00.084 --> 12:01.538
I'm already
in their crosshairs.

12:01.586 --> 12:02.802
And now that
I know what happened,

12:02.849 --> 12:04.513
I might as well have been
a part of it myself.

12:04.560 --> 12:05.834
Then maybe
instead of poking the bear,

12:05.881 --> 12:07.481
we should tell Mike Ross
the truth.

12:07.614 --> 12:09.004
What are you talking about?

12:09.052 --> 12:10.997
We both know that Mike is not
going to let this thing go

12:11.044 --> 12:12.268
till he gets to
the bottom of it.

12:12.315 --> 12:13.544
Maybe, if I just come clean...

12:13.592 --> 12:14.622
listen to me, Alex.

12:14.670 --> 12:15.755
You go to him with your story,

12:15.802 --> 12:17.234
you're going to give him
a map to what happened,

12:17.281 --> 12:18.379
a can of gas, and a match

12:18.427 --> 12:20.427
to light the whole damn thing
on fire.

12:21.267 --> 12:24.168
I hope you're right, Harvey,
because I've got a daughter,

12:24.248 --> 12:26.464
and if I didn't take a chance to
stop this thing when I had it...

12:26.511 --> 12:28.637
I'm telling you, Alex,
you let it go.

12:28.976 --> 12:32.661
♪♪

12:32.708 --> 12:36.153
♪♪

12:36.421 --> 12:37.872
- Harvey.
- Louis.

12:37.987 --> 12:39.700
Jessica said
hardman wants us to work

12:39.748 --> 12:41.278
on the reinsdorf case
together.

12:41.356 --> 12:42.474
She said the same thing to me.

12:42.521 --> 12:45.286
Well, I'm here to help,
not get in a fight.

12:45.372 --> 12:46.551
My feelings exactly.

12:46.618 --> 12:49.786
Good, I thought we could start
by talking strategy.

12:50.223 --> 12:51.540
I'm sorry,
but are you first chair?

12:51.587 --> 12:52.934
No, you are,
but I just thought...

12:52.982 --> 12:54.201
doesn't matter
what you thought,

12:54.248 --> 12:56.529
because our strategy is to go
after their general counsel.

12:57.479 --> 12:59.336
And when would you like
to depose this guy?

12:59.384 --> 13:01.385
Never, because I'm going to
put that asshole on the stand,

13:01.432 --> 13:03.650
and I'm going to crack him like
a piece of matzo on passover.

13:03.697 --> 13:06.397
Louis, you put him on
the stand without deposing him,

13:06.469 --> 13:08.596
you'll be asking questions
you don't know the answers to.

13:08.643 --> 13:09.689
- So what?
- So,

13:09.737 --> 13:11.306
that's the number one rule
of lawyering.

13:11.354 --> 13:12.838
Well, thank you,
F. Lee Bailey.

13:12.886 --> 13:13.948
And here I thought
the number one rule

13:13.995 --> 13:15.478
was to know your goddamn place.

13:15.539 --> 13:17.790
And I don't need to take advice
from a sixth-year associate.

13:17.837 --> 13:19.719
And I don't need to take
a loss on my record

13:19.775 --> 13:21.478
because you're too insecure
to listen to reason.

13:21.525 --> 13:23.016
You know what, Harvey,
you don't need to take anything

13:23.063 --> 13:24.516
because you're not in charge.

13:24.564 --> 13:26.946
So it's up to you:
You gonna get on board

13:26.994 --> 13:28.394
or are you gonna
go crying to mama?

13:28.550 --> 13:31.141
♪♪

13:31.227 --> 13:33.327
You're right, Louis.
You're the partner.

13:33.550 --> 13:35.317
I'm just here to back you up.

13:35.413 --> 13:37.727
♪♪

13:37.891 --> 13:40.696
Donna, I want you to pull
whatever strings you have to

13:40.751 --> 13:43.438
to get the reinsdorf trial
moved up to tomorrow.

13:43.520 --> 13:44.695
I'll get right on it.

13:44.743 --> 13:47.297
And one more thing:
Don't tell Louis.

13:47.345 --> 13:48.544
What?
Harvey,

13:48.592 --> 13:50.289
Jessica said
to bury the hatchet,

13:50.357 --> 13:51.578
not stick it in Louis's back.

13:51.626 --> 13:53.383
Donna, I went into his office
in good faith

13:53.469 --> 13:54.819
and it took him
less than 30 seconds

13:54.866 --> 13:56.211
to wave his title in my face.

13:56.259 --> 13:58.040
What does that have to do
with putting the firm's interest

13:58.087 --> 13:59.152
above your ego?

13:59.200 --> 14:01.024
Because, when I brought up
a legitimate issue

14:01.072 --> 14:03.515
with his strategy, he shot me
down for no other reason

14:03.563 --> 14:04.844
than it came out of my mouth.

14:04.892 --> 14:07.430
I'm telling you: We don't
do this, we're going to lose.

14:08.805 --> 14:10.524
Look at me.

14:11.063 --> 14:12.515
Are you sure
this is the right call?

14:12.604 --> 14:13.961
Listen to me.
Jessica wants me

14:14.009 --> 14:15.929
to play the long game,
and that's what I'm doing.

14:16.031 --> 14:18.565
I sat in there, ate shit,
and he bought it.

14:18.723 --> 14:21.086
So now, tomorrow,
I'm going to win this thing,

14:21.459 --> 14:24.227
and Jessica's going to know
she can count on me.

14:24.579 --> 14:26.078
All right.

14:26.275 --> 14:27.875
I'll move the court date,

14:28.166 --> 14:30.133
and I'll make sure
Louis doesn't find out.

14:30.235 --> 14:33.446
♪♪

14:33.493 --> 14:36.360
♪♪

14:36.507 --> 14:38.102
Harvey, good, you're here.

14:38.727 --> 14:40.719
We didn't get a chance to
talk about what happened

14:40.805 --> 14:42.078
with you, Alex, and Mike.

14:42.126 --> 14:43.851
No, we didn't,
and as a matter of fact,

14:43.899 --> 14:45.274
I'm wondering where Mike is.

14:45.407 --> 14:47.813
Well, he was in earlier,
but then he left.

14:47.899 --> 14:49.789
But I'm guessing
that's not really

14:49.875 --> 14:51.180
the question you're asking.

14:51.285 --> 14:53.563
You want to know if he's
somehow still pursing that case.

14:53.641 --> 14:55.125
And what if I do?

14:55.309 --> 14:57.609
I would say
from personal experience,

14:57.782 --> 14:59.037
don't ask a question unless

14:59.085 --> 15:00.652
you're really ready
to hear the answer.

15:01.199 --> 15:05.024
♪♪

15:08.086 --> 15:09.696
What the hell
do you think you're doing?

15:09.744 --> 15:10.874
Jessica, how did you know?

15:10.928 --> 15:11.944
It doesn't matter how.

15:11.992 --> 15:14.064
What matters is, I told you
to work it out with Louis,

15:14.111 --> 15:15.695
and right now,
he's sitting in his office

15:15.742 --> 15:17.458
with no idea
this case is starting.

15:17.536 --> 15:19.913
Exactly, I'm playing
the long game, like you said.

15:19.961 --> 15:20.992
No, Harvey.

15:21.040 --> 15:22.226
You're not playing anything,

15:22.300 --> 15:23.566
because this case is mine now.

15:23.614 --> 15:24.646
- What?
- You heard me.

15:24.727 --> 15:25.952
I gave you a direct order,

15:26.015 --> 15:27.617
and you spat in my face.

15:27.665 --> 15:29.265
Jessica, this is bullshit.

15:29.327 --> 15:31.450
I went in there
and he spat in my face,

15:31.584 --> 15:33.949
and I was willing to take it,
but what I'm not willing to take

15:33.996 --> 15:35.590
is losing this thing
out of spite,

15:35.638 --> 15:37.442
and if you take this case
right now,

15:37.490 --> 15:38.771
you're going to lose,
because you have no idea

15:38.818 --> 15:41.006
- what's going on with it.
- Maybe I will and maybe I won't.

15:41.053 --> 15:42.541
But sometimes you have to
bench your quarterback

15:42.588 --> 15:43.997
to show 'em
who's running the team,

15:44.045 --> 15:45.544
whether you take a loss or not.

15:45.658 --> 15:46.887
All rise!

15:47.010 --> 15:49.020
Time's up, Harvey.
Step aside.

15:49.162 --> 15:51.150
Jessica, please don't do this
to me in public.

15:51.254 --> 15:52.947
I'm not doing anything to you.

15:53.126 --> 15:55.243
You did this to yourself.

15:55.805 --> 15:57.297
Do we have a problem,
counselor?

15:57.345 --> 15:58.638
No, your honor, we don't.

15:58.741 --> 16:00.507
My colleague is needed
back at our firm.

16:00.555 --> 16:02.055
I'm stepping in.

16:02.548 --> 16:04.344
In that case,
be seated, everyone.

16:04.860 --> 16:06.594
Court is now in session.

16:08.382 --> 16:10.014
♪♪

16:14.905 --> 16:16.423
Michael,
why are you closing the door?

16:16.471 --> 16:18.190
You know I'm uncomfortable
with obstructed exits.

16:18.237 --> 16:19.637
Because I need to
ask you something,

16:19.692 --> 16:21.384
and I don't want
to be interrupted.

16:24.139 --> 16:26.401
Michael, you're asking me to
hack a government institution.

16:26.448 --> 16:28.610
- I can't do that.
- Look closely, Benjamin.

16:29.404 --> 16:31.467
It's a private corporation,
and I'm telling you,

16:31.594 --> 16:33.459
they're scumbags.

16:34.449 --> 16:35.724
What's it for?

16:35.998 --> 16:37.107
What do you mean?

16:37.420 --> 16:39.567
I mean, if you're asking me
to do something like this,

16:39.615 --> 16:41.138
I have to bill it to a case.

16:41.217 --> 16:42.521
And what if I asked you
not to?

16:42.607 --> 16:44.059
I would have to ask you why.

16:44.107 --> 16:46.037
I'm going against
Harvey's wishes.

16:47.185 --> 16:49.021
You asked me to do that
once before

16:49.114 --> 16:50.271
for a mock trial.

16:50.365 --> 16:52.426
And I need to know,
is this mock, or is it real?

16:52.474 --> 16:53.481
It's real,

16:53.536 --> 16:54.763
and Harvey can't know.

16:54.817 --> 16:57.438
♪♪<i> Tense music...</i>

16:57.831 --> 17:00.177
♪♪

17:01.522 --> 17:04.089
Harvey, I didn't think you
ever got south of canal street.

17:04.137 --> 17:06.536
Yeah, well,
today I'm making an exception.

17:06.942 --> 17:08.324
Is that offer
still on the table?

17:08.380 --> 17:09.512
Are you serious?

17:09.598 --> 17:10.739
I'm here, aren't I?

17:10.825 --> 17:12.606
Then hell yeah,
it's still on the table.

17:13.184 --> 17:14.637
I'll talk to Tommy Bratton
right now.

17:14.786 --> 17:16.294
Well, when you talk to him,

17:16.355 --> 17:19.035
you tell him I'm only coming
over if he meets my demands.

17:19.083 --> 17:20.380
And what demands
would those be?

17:20.428 --> 17:21.880
I don't just want partner.
I want an office with a view.

17:21.926 --> 17:24.800
I want to eat what I kill
and I want to get paid

17:24.848 --> 17:26.903
more than any other
junior partner in the firm.

17:27.231 --> 17:28.747
Those are some
pretty big asks.

17:28.817 --> 17:30.652
I can't guarantee Bratton's
going to say yes.

17:30.700 --> 17:33.474
You want to make partner on my
coattails, you make him say yes.

17:33.522 --> 17:35.035
- Your coattails?
- I'm talking about

17:35.083 --> 17:36.598
me helping you
as much as about you helping me.

17:36.645 --> 17:38.049
Then do what you said
you were going to do,

17:38.096 --> 17:39.365
because if you can't
make that happen,

17:39.412 --> 17:41.692
they don't respect me,
and I'm not coming to a place

17:41.773 --> 17:42.934
where I'm not respected.

17:42.982 --> 17:44.882
Okay, Harvey,
but if you want respect,

17:44.930 --> 17:46.434
you need to show
some damn respect.

17:46.482 --> 17:47.966
I go in to stick my neck
out for you,

17:48.056 --> 17:49.802
you don't come back
and say you'll consider it.

17:49.849 --> 17:51.911
It's a done goddamn deal.

17:52.633 --> 17:54.395
Okay, Alex, you have my word.

17:54.443 --> 17:58.045
You get me everything
I'm asking for...

17:58.351 --> 18:00.106
I'm done with Pearson Hardman.

18:00.170 --> 18:03.739
♪♪

18:03.910 --> 18:05.409
Jessica.
Hey, how are ya?

18:05.551 --> 18:07.497
Louis, remember
when we talked about

18:07.545 --> 18:09.364
not abusing your power
with Harvey?

18:09.435 --> 18:10.693
Absolutely,
and that's why I treated him

18:10.740 --> 18:11.630
with the utmost respect.

18:11.678 --> 18:13.184
Well, if that's the case,
then exactly

18:13.232 --> 18:15.333
why did he litigate reinsdorf
behind your back?

18:15.411 --> 18:17.247
Goddamn it.
What the hell did he do?

18:17.326 --> 18:18.942
I'm not concerned with
what he did.

18:19.006 --> 18:20.107
I'm concerned with what you did.

18:20.154 --> 18:21.834
Jessica, I swear,
I was the perfect gentleman,

18:21.881 --> 18:23.781
but then Harvey questioned
my leadership.

18:23.900 --> 18:25.369
In other words,
he had a better idea than you?

18:25.416 --> 18:27.049
Well, whether it was
or it wasn't,

18:27.097 --> 18:28.966
he didn't respect
the office of junior partner.

18:29.014 --> 18:31.325
Because there is no office
of junior partner, Louis,

18:31.422 --> 18:33.239
and the real problem here
isn't Harvey.

18:33.287 --> 18:34.958
It's that chip
on your shoulder.

18:35.025 --> 18:36.177
What chip?

18:37.094 --> 18:38.583
Louis, I need you to be
at this address

18:38.630 --> 18:40.411
tomorrow morning at 9:00 A.M.

18:40.459 --> 18:41.582
- Why?
- Because I believe

18:41.630 --> 18:43.263
you will benefit
from therapy,

18:43.391 --> 18:44.865
and this man is the best
in the business.

18:44.912 --> 18:46.312
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
back the truck up.

18:46.387 --> 18:48.020
Jessica, therapy?

18:48.219 --> 18:49.926
I'm the most stable,
secure man you ever met.

18:49.973 --> 18:50.942
And you fight me on this,

18:50.990 --> 18:52.584
you'll be the most
unemployed man I've ever met.

18:52.631 --> 18:54.030
Do we understand each other?

18:54.346 --> 18:55.747
Yeah.
9:00 A.M. it is.

18:55.997 --> 18:57.083
And Louis,

18:57.131 --> 18:58.372
when you walk
through that door,

18:58.420 --> 19:00.699
you're going to be tempted to
turn right the hell around,

19:00.965 --> 19:03.285
and I'm telling you,
if you want a future here,

19:03.692 --> 19:04.692
you won't.

19:04.802 --> 19:06.865
♪♪

19:08.279 --> 19:10.693
♪♪

19:11.358 --> 19:12.989
Harvey,
what are you doing here?

19:13.037 --> 19:14.263
I thought you were in court
all day.

19:14.310 --> 19:15.707
Well, Jessica had other plans,

19:15.755 --> 19:17.325
like booting me off this case.

19:17.373 --> 19:18.417
What?

19:18.474 --> 19:20.309
She walked in there
and threw me out

19:20.357 --> 19:21.724
with my tail between my legs,

19:21.779 --> 19:24.146
like I was a piece-of-shit
first-year associate.

19:24.263 --> 19:26.428
Listen to me, you need to
calm down so we can figure out

19:26.475 --> 19:27.309
what we're going to do.

19:27.357 --> 19:28.396
I am calm,

19:28.444 --> 19:30.584
and I already took care
of what we're going to do.

19:30.848 --> 19:32.693
What are you talking about?

19:34.374 --> 19:36.396
I got us an offer
at Bratton gould.

19:36.513 --> 19:38.084
If everything goes like I think,

19:38.132 --> 19:39.250
we'll be there
by the end of the week.

19:39.297 --> 19:40.364
- What?
- Harvey,

19:40.412 --> 19:41.646
that doesn't make any sense.

19:41.716 --> 19:43.060
Jessica's your biggest fan.

19:43.123 --> 19:44.233
She's always been
in your corner.

19:44.280 --> 19:46.278
Was she in my corner
when hardman promoted Louis?

19:46.326 --> 19:47.713
That's not fair.
That was his call.

19:47.761 --> 19:49.183
Well, whose call was
cutting my balls off

19:49.230 --> 19:50.667
in front of
the entire courtroom today?

19:50.714 --> 19:52.017
I don't care what she did.

19:52.065 --> 19:53.775
The woman paid for you
to go to law school

19:53.853 --> 19:54.759
out of her own pocket.

19:54.861 --> 19:56.182
The least you can do
is talk to her

19:56.229 --> 19:57.438
before you do something
like this.

19:57.485 --> 19:58.930
Donna, I tried talking to her.

19:58.978 --> 20:00.752
But it doesn't matter.
It's too late.

20:00.869 --> 20:02.946
I gave Alex my word.
It's a done deal.

20:02.994 --> 20:05.564
♪♪

20:06.010 --> 20:08.300
Well, it may be
a done deal for you,

20:09.041 --> 20:10.627
but it isn't a done deal for me.

20:10.697 --> 20:12.350
- Donna...
- I like it here, Harvey,

20:12.509 --> 20:14.119
and you can't just
make this kind of decision

20:14.166 --> 20:16.103
about my life without
running it by me first.

20:16.197 --> 20:18.258
If this is your way of trying
to get me to stay...

20:18.313 --> 20:20.625
I'm not trying to get you
to do anything,

20:20.681 --> 20:22.500
but I'm not just gonna
follow you out the door

20:22.548 --> 20:23.486
without thinking this through.

20:23.534 --> 20:25.294
What do you want, Donna?
You want an apology?

20:25.402 --> 20:27.775
Well, here it is: I'm sorry
I didn't consult with you.

20:27.915 --> 20:30.236
I don't want an apology,
Harvey.

20:30.720 --> 20:33.078
I wanted to talk this thing
through with you,

20:33.126 --> 20:35.527
which, by the way, is what you
should have done with Jessica.

20:35.900 --> 20:37.173
Well, you know what, Donna?

20:37.353 --> 20:38.930
I didn't come to you for advice.

20:38.978 --> 20:41.412
I came to tell you
to start packing.

20:41.790 --> 20:43.490
But if you don't want
to come with me,

20:43.538 --> 20:44.937
then don't come with me.

20:44.984 --> 20:47.517
♪♪

20:49.197 --> 20:53.080
♪♪

20:54.166 --> 20:55.760
Rachel, do you have a second?

20:56.283 --> 20:57.395
Of course.

20:57.658 --> 20:59.166
Mike went to prison for me.

20:59.260 --> 21:01.553
I owe him, and I know it.

21:01.978 --> 21:03.799
But he's not the only guy I owe,

21:03.924 --> 21:05.724
and that guy's going to have
a serious problem

21:05.783 --> 21:07.087
if I stick my head in the sand,

21:07.135 --> 21:09.502
pretending Mike isn't
who I know he really is.

21:09.635 --> 21:11.627
That's a shitty situation
to be in.

21:11.713 --> 21:14.024
Yeah, it is, so I'm going
to ask you something,

21:14.072 --> 21:16.213
but I need you
to be honest with me.

21:17.494 --> 21:19.908
Is Mike still working on
the case against reform corp.?

21:20.080 --> 21:21.938
He is.
And for the record, Harvey,

21:21.986 --> 21:23.322
he told me that if you asked,

21:23.383 --> 21:25.047
to tell you everything
you wanted to know.

21:25.096 --> 21:26.478
What exactly is he doing?

21:26.559 --> 21:28.228
He's trying to build
a criminal case

21:28.291 --> 21:29.173
to give to Anita Gibbs,

21:29.221 --> 21:30.462
which he has every right to do.

21:30.510 --> 21:31.650
Because the agreement
he signed

21:31.697 --> 21:33.088
only precluded a civil suit.

21:33.181 --> 21:34.752
Exactly.

21:35.494 --> 21:36.667
How far along is he?

21:36.715 --> 21:38.088
I don't know,
but knowing Mike,

21:38.171 --> 21:39.696
I'm sure
he's a hell of a lot closer

21:39.744 --> 21:41.119
than he was this morning.

21:41.205 --> 21:43.330
♪♪

21:43.580 --> 21:44.774
What do you think?

21:44.822 --> 21:47.103
Do you want to share
a bottle of rosé?

21:48.003 --> 21:49.869
I think I remember
what happened the last time

21:49.917 --> 21:50.774
we did that.

21:50.822 --> 21:52.510
All the more reason
to get it, then.

21:54.072 --> 21:55.414
I couldn't agree more.

21:55.767 --> 21:58.689
Good, now that
that is decided...

22:02.322 --> 22:04.228
Happy anniversary.

22:04.497 --> 22:07.299
♪♪ Lounge music playing...

22:07.500 --> 22:10.835
♪ ♪

22:11.002 --> 22:12.416
Shakespeare's sonnets.

22:12.464 --> 22:13.892
Everyone is talking
about this guy.

22:13.940 --> 22:15.549
Apparently
he's all the rage right now.

22:17.214 --> 22:19.049
This was my favorite class
in college.

22:19.097 --> 22:20.228
How did you know?

22:20.306 --> 22:21.596
I do my homework.

22:22.197 --> 22:23.706
Thank you.

22:23.971 --> 22:27.510
♪ ♪

22:27.877 --> 22:29.361
- what?
- Nothing.

22:29.424 --> 22:31.089
It's just so nice
to be with a man

22:31.174 --> 22:33.282
who's so thoughtful after
spending all day with a man

22:33.411 --> 22:34.806
who doesn't even know
what the word means.

22:34.853 --> 22:36.033
Talking about Harvey.

22:36.081 --> 22:37.322
He's leaving the firm,
and he just assumed

22:37.369 --> 22:38.838
that I would go with him.

22:38.939 --> 22:40.631
He didn't even think
to ask me first.

22:40.713 --> 22:42.037
We're celebrating tonight.

22:42.111 --> 22:43.588
Let's not talk about Harvey.

22:43.636 --> 22:45.525
I'm not talking about Harvey;
I'm talking about my life,

22:45.572 --> 22:47.192
and a huge decision
that I have to make.

22:47.333 --> 22:49.213
Wait a second... you're actually
thinking about going with him?

22:49.260 --> 22:50.576
Even after the way
he treated you?

22:50.623 --> 22:52.025
I don't know
what I'm going to do.

22:52.073 --> 22:53.588
Well, what if I said that
I'd like you to stay

22:53.635 --> 22:55.229
- at Pearson Hardman?
- Why would you say that?

22:55.276 --> 22:57.485
- You know why.
- Because Harvey's like a

22:57.533 --> 22:59.313
silent partner
in our relationship.

22:59.361 --> 23:00.564
I mean, we can't even get
through a dinner

23:00.611 --> 23:01.447
without his name coming up.

23:01.495 --> 23:05.063
Mark, I specifically told him
not to interrupt us tonight

23:05.111 --> 23:06.680
so he wouldn't come up.

23:06.728 --> 23:08.502
And yet he came up anyway.

23:08.830 --> 23:10.148
- Mark...
- Look,

23:10.346 --> 23:11.869
I don't pretend to be
as insightful as you are,

23:11.916 --> 23:14.267
but if you can't even separate
yourself from him

23:14.651 --> 23:17.830
when he's asking you to leave
a job that you love...

23:18.705 --> 23:21.306
Makes me wonder if it's really
the job you love after all.

23:21.455 --> 23:22.752
What do you want me to say,
Mark?

23:22.806 --> 23:24.775
I want you to say that you're
not going to follow the guy

23:24.822 --> 23:27.424
wherever he goes
for the rest of your life.

23:28.611 --> 23:30.477
I'm not going to say that.

23:32.352 --> 23:34.415
Okay, well, I guess
I have my answer, then.

23:34.571 --> 23:37.155
♪♪<i> Somber music...</i>

23:37.422 --> 23:41.225
♪♪

23:48.460 --> 23:51.500
- Rachel, you are not going to believe...
- Mike, before you say anything...

23:51.548 --> 23:54.163
Harvey asked me if you were
still going after reform corp.,

23:54.211 --> 23:55.655
and I told him that you were.

23:55.703 --> 23:56.990
Doesn't matter,
'cause I got 'em.

23:57.038 --> 23:58.397
What?

23:58.892 --> 24:02.202
Gallo told me that Masterson
was using reform corp.'S inmates

24:02.250 --> 24:03.287
to build new prisons.

24:03.335 --> 24:05.827
Okay, but using inmates for
private companies is illegal.

24:05.944 --> 24:07.366
It would be,
except five years ago,

24:07.414 --> 24:10.140
Alex Williams got a waiver from
the state corrections board

24:10.234 --> 24:12.546
allowing them to supplement
their workforce with inmates.

24:12.603 --> 24:14.304
So where's the crime?

24:18.064 --> 24:19.616
Wait a second.
Why are Masterson's budgets

24:19.663 --> 24:21.054
on reform corp.'S email server?

24:21.102 --> 24:23.382
More importantly,
why are the labor costs

24:23.452 --> 24:25.733
1/5 of what they submitted
to the state?

24:25.868 --> 24:27.108
Jesus.

24:27.186 --> 24:29.020
Mike, they didn't just
use the inmates to supplement

24:29.067 --> 24:30.897
the workforce;
The inmates were the workforce.

24:30.945 --> 24:33.078
Which means reform corp.'S
not just extending sentences,

24:33.125 --> 24:34.569
they're defrauding the state,

24:34.617 --> 24:36.944
and they're splitting the
profits with Masterson, 50/50.

24:37.136 --> 24:38.398
Mike,
where did you get all this?

24:38.445 --> 24:39.500
- What does that matter?
- It matters because

24:39.547 --> 24:41.725
if it came from Masterson,

24:41.812 --> 24:43.587
then Harvey can stop Anita Gibbs
from using it.

24:43.634 --> 24:44.843
Well, it didn't.

24:45.117 --> 24:46.950
Benjamin got it from
reform corp.'S server,

24:46.998 --> 24:49.177
which means we can redact
Masterson, give it to Gibbs,

24:49.225 --> 24:50.627
and she can put the pieces
together herself.

24:50.674 --> 24:53.327
There is nothing that
Harvey can do about it.

24:54.137 --> 24:55.536
Mike,
he could fire you for this.

24:55.757 --> 24:57.585
Rachel, I've been torn up
trying to reconcile

24:57.640 --> 24:59.968
two parts of myself for
as long as I can remember:

25:00.016 --> 25:02.317
Pro Bono versus corporate law.

25:02.453 --> 25:04.202
♪♪ <i>Tense music...</i>

25:04.253 --> 25:07.007
If he lets me go,
then he lets me go.

25:07.178 --> 25:10.921
♪♪

25:16.666 --> 25:18.061
Hello?

25:21.296 --> 25:23.164
Hi, I'm Louis litt,

25:23.251 --> 25:25.384
here for
my 9:00 A.M. appointment.

25:27.425 --> 25:28.879
Hello?

25:29.107 --> 25:30.574
Hi, ya, Mr. litt.

25:30.730 --> 25:32.949
We've been expecting you.

25:35.318 --> 25:37.558
I'm sorry, but did you just
speak in a German accent?

25:37.730 --> 25:38.980
Please, taken ze seat.

25:39.028 --> 25:41.152
Holy shit,
you're a goddamn Nazi.

25:43.965 --> 25:45.269
What did you just say to me?

25:45.317 --> 25:46.886
I said
I'm not going to sit here

25:47.027 --> 25:48.044
and talk to you about
the weather,

25:48.091 --> 25:49.660
let alone my goddamn feelings.

25:49.816 --> 25:51.886
Thanks, but no thanks,
Wiener Schnitzel.

25:52.202 --> 25:54.379
Please, Louis.

25:55.081 --> 25:57.214
Just give me two minutes.

25:58.607 --> 26:00.475
Two minutes.

26:03.127 --> 26:04.427
First of all...

26:04.746 --> 26:06.160
I take it you're Jewish?

26:06.292 --> 26:07.858
Yeah, I'm not comfortable
answering that right now.

26:07.905 --> 26:09.168
Well, it seems very clear,

26:09.216 --> 26:11.574
based on the fact that
you just called me a Nazi.

26:11.691 --> 26:13.004
What's your point?

26:13.052 --> 26:14.889
Would it interest you to know
that I'm Jewish too?

26:14.936 --> 26:16.446
Yeah, well, take out
your circumcised junk,

26:16.493 --> 26:17.410
and maybe I'll believe you.

26:17.458 --> 26:18.816
I'm not going to do that,
Louis.

26:18.864 --> 26:21.763
But, ,, I will tell you
that my parents

26:21.832 --> 26:23.886
were both children
during the war.

26:25.269 --> 26:28.207
They survived by fleeing the
country and felt it their duty

26:28.305 --> 26:31.699
to eventually return and raise
both my sister and myself

26:31.894 --> 26:33.763
as proud Germans and Jews.

26:33.894 --> 26:35.347
So, if you want to leave

26:35.395 --> 26:36.800
because you don't like
the way I speak,

26:36.847 --> 26:38.449
I understand, but if not,

26:38.808 --> 26:41.347
why don't you tell me
what brings you here?

26:45.322 --> 26:47.715
♪♪

26:47.856 --> 26:50.857
I'm here because
no matter what I do,

26:51.148 --> 26:52.855
nobody respects me.

26:53.171 --> 26:55.805
♪♪

26:55.862 --> 26:57.211
Jessica, we need to talk.

26:57.322 --> 26:58.511
We do.

26:58.604 --> 26:59.926
But if you're looking
for an apology...

26:59.973 --> 27:01.238
I'm not here for an apology.

27:01.316 --> 27:03.519
I'm here to tell you that
I'm expecting a job offer

27:03.674 --> 27:04.925
from Bratton Gould.

27:05.063 --> 27:06.896
You're expecting one...

27:07.219 --> 27:08.585
Or you went looking for one?

27:08.666 --> 27:10.371
- Does it matter?
- It does to me.

27:10.580 --> 27:13.514
Then you should know, I was
offered a job, I turned it down,

27:13.562 --> 27:15.269
and it was going to
stay turned down

27:15.348 --> 27:17.282
until you made it
crystal clear

27:17.370 --> 27:18.550
that you don't respect me.

27:18.598 --> 27:21.232
What I made clear is that
I call the shots,

27:21.398 --> 27:23.313
and if you don't see how that
helps you in the long run...

27:23.360 --> 27:25.199
screw the long run!

27:25.650 --> 27:28.160
They're going to make me
a partner now.

27:29.379 --> 27:30.996
You won't even
go to bat for me.

27:31.069 --> 27:32.230
You know what, Harvey?

27:32.289 --> 27:34.480
I'm about done with
your little song and dance

27:34.528 --> 27:35.808
about how
I don't have your back.

27:35.873 --> 27:38.605
I picked you
out of the goddamn mail room,

27:38.783 --> 27:41.450
and I've given you every
opportunity you ever had.

27:41.835 --> 27:42.955
This was a mistake.

27:43.035 --> 27:44.164
What was a mistake?

27:44.221 --> 27:45.609
I came here
to give you a chance

27:45.716 --> 27:47.180
to talk me out of leaving,

27:47.253 --> 27:49.195
but when this offer comes in,
it's too late.

27:49.340 --> 27:50.406
Just out of curiosity,

27:50.454 --> 27:51.602
what would you have me do?

27:51.676 --> 27:54.141
You know what the hell
I'd have you do.

27:55.000 --> 27:57.320
Harvey,
you have more raw talent

27:57.648 --> 28:00.328
than 99% of the partners
in this firm,

28:00.376 --> 28:02.640
but I'm not going to give you
a promotion based on a threat.

28:02.687 --> 28:04.133
You'll get one
when you're ready.

28:04.236 --> 28:06.320
And if that's not good enough
for you...

28:06.774 --> 28:08.837
Then I wish you luck
at Bratton Gould.

28:08.961 --> 28:11.836
Then consider this
my official notice.

28:11.984 --> 28:14.951
♪♪

28:16.078 --> 28:19.086
Louis, we spent
the last 40 minutes going over

28:19.134 --> 28:20.883
every person
who has shown you disrespect

28:20.968 --> 28:22.101
since the day you were born.

28:22.149 --> 28:23.529
You kidding?
I'm just getting started.

28:23.576 --> 28:25.444
Be that as it may,

28:26.085 --> 28:28.118
if I ask you the one person

28:28.190 --> 28:29.921
whose respect
you crave the most,

28:29.969 --> 28:31.062
who would it be?

28:31.110 --> 28:33.179
Don't dwell on it.
Just say the first name

28:33.227 --> 28:34.226
that pops into your head.

28:34.274 --> 28:35.296
Harvey Specter.

28:35.344 --> 28:37.155
Good.
What's he like?

28:37.358 --> 28:40.443
He's like a cross between
Marlon Brando and superman.

28:42.568 --> 28:43.975
What?

28:44.332 --> 28:46.131
I'm just picturing.

28:48.169 --> 28:50.369
This Harvey, is he a friend?

28:50.465 --> 28:51.946
He's my best friend.

28:51.994 --> 28:54.294
Would he describe you
as his best friend?

28:54.969 --> 28:56.298
What the... what the fu...
Is that supposed to mean?

28:56.345 --> 28:57.798
- Louis...
- You son of a bitch.

28:57.854 --> 28:59.275
Are you implying that
I'm not as good as him?

28:59.322 --> 29:00.188
That I'm worthless?

29:00.236 --> 29:02.032
Well you know what,
you Nazi supposed Jew,

29:02.080 --> 29:03.291
I don't need to take that
from you.

29:03.338 --> 29:04.555
I'm goddamn out of here!

29:04.603 --> 29:06.329
Louis, this is wonderful.

29:06.378 --> 29:07.674
What the hell
are you talking about?

29:07.721 --> 29:10.673
Most people take years
to reveal their true selves.

29:10.801 --> 29:13.902
But you, you are like a man
without skin.

29:13.985 --> 29:15.937
I can see right through you.

29:15.993 --> 29:17.313
This is fantastic.

29:17.374 --> 29:19.134
How the hell
is this fantastic?

29:19.225 --> 29:20.930
Because I can help you.

29:20.978 --> 29:23.454
Your feelings of disrespect
are internal,

29:23.502 --> 29:26.118
and you project them
onto the people in front of you,

29:26.230 --> 29:27.729
and in your life,

29:27.905 --> 29:30.606
those people throw
that disrespect back at you.

29:30.654 --> 29:33.742
Well, I'm not going
to do that to you.

29:33.923 --> 29:35.477
I'm going to be here for you.

29:35.579 --> 29:36.821
That sounds like
a load of crap.

29:36.869 --> 29:37.884
Listen to me.

29:37.932 --> 29:40.259
If you keep treating the people
in your life like this,

29:40.564 --> 29:42.735
you're going to push them away.

29:44.227 --> 29:46.016
You know what, doc?

29:46.432 --> 29:49.967
Jessica made me come here,
and I did.

29:50.165 --> 29:53.305
And now that I have,
it's crystal clear

29:53.477 --> 29:55.965
the last thing I need
in the world is therapy.

29:56.180 --> 29:59.626
♪♪

29:59.673 --> 30:01.673
♪♪

30:02.919 --> 30:05.053
Louis, calm down, you're
wearing a hole in the carpet.

30:05.133 --> 30:07.025
Well, I'm sorry, Donna, Harvey
called an emergency meeting.

30:07.072 --> 30:09.430
- What do you expect?
- I expect a little self-control.

30:09.593 --> 30:11.118
Good, you're here.

30:11.237 --> 30:12.695
Gretchen said it couldn't
wait... what's going on?

30:12.742 --> 30:15.476
I've got a move I want
to make, but before I do,

30:15.915 --> 30:17.276
I want to put it to a vote.

30:17.324 --> 30:18.782
- What kind of move?
- A big one.

30:18.830 --> 30:20.431
Harvey, does this have
something to do with the fight

30:20.478 --> 30:21.710
between you, Alex, and Mike?

30:21.767 --> 30:23.384
Yes,
and I have reason to believe

30:23.432 --> 30:24.501
that fight's not over.

30:24.549 --> 30:26.486
- Harvey, what's going on?
- Alex has a gun to his head,

30:26.533 --> 30:27.611
and if I don't do something
about it,

30:27.658 --> 30:29.266
he's going to be in
some deep shit.

30:29.356 --> 30:30.524
I have a way out of it,

30:30.572 --> 30:32.196
but there's going to be
some consequences.

30:32.243 --> 30:33.391
- For who?
- For Mike.

30:33.439 --> 30:35.088
Harvey, is there any
other way out of this mess?

30:35.135 --> 30:36.970
If there were,
I wouldn't be standing here.

30:37.087 --> 30:38.244
Then tell us
what you want to do,

30:38.291 --> 30:39.837
and let's get this over with.

30:40.724 --> 30:44.376
♪♪

30:44.860 --> 30:47.298
Don't tell me this is the "two
partners for the price of one"

30:47.352 --> 30:48.751
idea you pitched me a year ago?

30:48.845 --> 30:50.625
It is, but Harvey Specter

30:50.673 --> 30:52.055
isn't like any lawyer
we've ever had.

30:52.102 --> 30:53.446
Well, he's better not be,

30:53.494 --> 30:56.829
if he has the balls to ask for
the moon and stars like this.

30:57.295 --> 30:59.149
Look, the problem is,
I already have an offer out

30:59.196 --> 31:00.399
to a hotshot at skadden.

31:00.460 --> 31:01.864
And if he hasn't already
said yes,

31:01.912 --> 31:03.188
what the hell
is he waiting for?

31:03.236 --> 31:06.070
I'll tell you what: He's afraid
he can't hack it here,

31:06.363 --> 31:08.227
or he's using us
to get a better offer.

31:08.298 --> 31:11.055
Either way, Harvey and I
are a better choice.

31:12.350 --> 31:13.851
All right, Alex.

31:14.034 --> 31:16.335
It looks like you two guys have
your shit together.

31:16.660 --> 31:17.772
But here's the thing:

31:17.904 --> 31:20.257
I pull this offer,
and your guy says no,

31:20.413 --> 31:22.937
I'm left here with nothing
but my dick in my hand.

31:23.055 --> 31:27.335
So you tell right now
you guarantee that he says yes.

31:27.436 --> 31:29.669
You think I didn't know
you were going to demand that?

31:29.999 --> 31:32.077
I already talked to him
about it.

31:32.306 --> 31:34.132
He gave me his word.

31:34.819 --> 31:37.820
Okay, looks like I have
two new partners.

31:39.030 --> 31:40.546
But Alex...

31:40.684 --> 31:43.418
This thing goes south, it's
your ass that's on the line.

31:43.694 --> 31:46.772
♪♪

31:47.217 --> 31:50.904
♪♪

31:51.030 --> 31:52.233
So you're having
a good coffee?

31:52.281 --> 31:54.171
Is that what we're doing
with our 11:00s now?

31:54.219 --> 31:55.468
Louis.

31:56.101 --> 31:57.358
What the hell is your problem?

31:57.406 --> 32:00.046
My problem is I found out
you moved my court dates,

32:00.094 --> 32:01.374
so why don't you go
tell your work husband

32:01.421 --> 32:02.686
if he thinks I'm going to
forget about this,

32:02.733 --> 32:03.819
he's got another thing coming.

32:03.866 --> 32:05.906
You know what, Louis?
Why don't you go tell him yourself?

32:05.953 --> 32:07.541
But you better hurry,
because as of Monday,

32:07.588 --> 32:09.488
Harvey doesn't work here
anymore.

32:10.366 --> 32:11.451
- What?
- You heard me.

32:11.499 --> 32:13.592
Harvey's leaving,
my life is a mess,

32:13.640 --> 32:16.303
and as far as I'm concerned,
that's on you.

32:16.351 --> 32:17.491
Me?
What do you mean, me?

32:17.624 --> 32:19.499
If you can't figure out
what I mean by that,

32:19.655 --> 32:21.592
then you may be
a good junior partner,

32:21.640 --> 32:24.124
but you got a long way to go
as a human being.

32:24.285 --> 32:27.286
♪♪ <i>Tense music...</i>

32:27.336 --> 32:30.991
♪♪

32:35.296 --> 32:36.577
What are you doing here?

32:36.624 --> 32:37.686
What do you mean,
what am I doing here?

32:37.733 --> 32:39.613
You wanted a conspiracy,
I got you one.

32:39.671 --> 32:42.263
I don't want anything
from you, and for the record,

32:42.311 --> 32:44.311
I was a fool to think I could
trust you in the first place.

32:44.358 --> 32:46.030
Anita, I don't know what
the hell you're talking about.

32:46.077 --> 32:47.115
Don't play dumb with me.

32:47.163 --> 32:49.357
Pearson Specter doesn't just
represent Masterson;

32:49.413 --> 32:51.194
you also represent Reform Corp.

32:51.257 --> 32:53.193
Which means anything
I get from you is tainted

32:53.241 --> 32:55.077
because you broke privilege.

32:55.226 --> 32:57.303
Goddamn it, Harvey must have
just signed them.

32:57.351 --> 32:58.382
So what you're saying is,

32:58.430 --> 33:00.670
Harvey was never on board
with this in the first place?

33:00.725 --> 33:02.710
Anita, you can still take
this case, all right?

33:02.758 --> 33:03.983
You just say you received
the evidence...

33:04.030 --> 33:05.967
Anonymously?
I don't think so, Mike.

33:06.015 --> 33:07.507
And one more thing:

33:07.647 --> 33:09.490
The next time you're looking
to involve me

33:09.538 --> 33:10.849
in a war with Harvey Specter,

33:10.897 --> 33:12.351
go to someone else.

33:12.421 --> 33:16.319
♪♪

33:19.386 --> 33:21.287
Jessica, I heard about Harvey.

33:21.381 --> 33:22.991
Louis, he made his choice.

33:23.051 --> 33:24.491
It's not the choice
that I wanted,

33:24.539 --> 33:26.879
but... we're just going to
have to deal with it.

33:26.927 --> 33:28.772
Now, if you don't mind...

33:29.050 --> 33:31.374
Well, actually, I do mind.

33:33.387 --> 33:35.366
Jessica, this whole thing
was my fault.

33:35.657 --> 33:38.102
I put him in a position where he
had to leave, and you know it.

33:38.149 --> 33:39.590
Louis, that's big of you,
but...

33:39.640 --> 33:40.499
Buy nothing.

33:40.547 --> 33:43.140
Doctor lipschitz said when
you don't respect yourself,

33:43.268 --> 33:45.835
you go looking for signs of
disrespect in others,

33:45.900 --> 33:48.296
and the way I got to
junior partner...

33:51.530 --> 33:53.116
I don't respect myself for that.

33:53.164 --> 33:54.327
What are you saying?

33:54.375 --> 33:57.084
I'm saying if it was my pride
in refusing to admit

33:57.132 --> 33:59.332
that he was right and I was
wrong that caused him to go,

33:59.397 --> 34:01.257
I won't be able to
forgive myself.

34:01.999 --> 34:04.671
So please, do not let him go.

34:09.022 --> 34:10.061
Louis?

34:10.210 --> 34:10.956
Yeah.

34:11.120 --> 34:13.154
♪♪ <i>Stirring pop music...</i>

34:13.248 --> 34:15.318
Did you mean what
you said the other day?

34:15.952 --> 34:18.418
About the associates needing
guidance and discipline?

34:18.538 --> 34:21.858
To tell you the truth,
I didn't at the time.

34:22.835 --> 34:24.061
But yes, they do.

34:24.172 --> 34:25.827
Then as the firm's
newest partner,

34:25.875 --> 34:29.155
how would you like to officially
be in charge of the associates?

34:29.277 --> 34:31.702
♪♪

34:31.899 --> 34:33.577
I'd like that very much.

34:34.114 --> 34:35.592
Treat them well.

34:36.491 --> 34:37.897
I will.

34:38.219 --> 34:41.952
♪♪

34:41.998 --> 34:45.819
♪♪

34:47.000 --> 34:53.074
Advertise your product or brand here
