34:54.772 --> 34:56.135
Did you come here to say
good-bye?

34:56.183 --> 34:57.975
Because I think
we already did that.

34:58.068 --> 34:59.358
No, Harvey.

34:59.448 --> 35:01.764
I came here to let you know
that I did what

35:01.905 --> 35:03.983
I should have done
in the first place.

35:04.794 --> 35:06.358
And what exactly
does that mean?

35:06.447 --> 35:09.014
It means I went to see
Daniel, and I told him

35:09.077 --> 35:12.518
if the next person we promote
to junior partner isn't you,

35:12.710 --> 35:14.444
I'm leaving.

35:15.092 --> 35:16.602
You did that for me?

35:16.650 --> 35:19.202
Sometimes playing the long
game means understanding

35:19.260 --> 35:21.427
who you want to be teammates
with in the long run,

35:21.577 --> 35:24.702
and the person I want to be
teammates with in the long run

35:24.975 --> 35:26.538
is you.

35:27.116 --> 35:31.116
I hope I'm not too late, Harvey,
but if I am,

35:31.677 --> 35:34.326
I really do wish you luck
at Bratton Gould.

35:34.880 --> 35:38.671
♪♪

35:38.718 --> 35:42.506
♪♪

35:48.241 --> 35:50.356
Harvey,
Alex Williams just called.

35:50.592 --> 35:52.217
Says it's a done deal.

35:52.360 --> 35:56.233
♪♪

35:56.443 --> 35:58.444
For the record,
I would have gone with you.

35:58.858 --> 36:01.921
For the record,
I should have asked you first.

36:02.099 --> 36:05.874
♪♪

36:05.921 --> 36:09.553
♪♪

36:12.732 --> 36:16.202
♪♪

36:18.811 --> 36:20.110
Hello?

36:20.158 --> 36:21.522
<i>Dr. lipschitz,
it's Louis litt.</i>

36:21.631 --> 36:23.210
Listen, you were right.

36:24.097 --> 36:26.522
I do need someone who isn't
going to let me push them away.

36:26.678 --> 36:28.225
I'm very happy to hear that,
Louis.

36:28.283 --> 36:30.049
Do you think five days a week
is too much?

36:30.139 --> 36:31.436
<i>Why don't we just</i>

36:31.577 --> 36:33.132
start with an appointment
on Monday

36:33.180 --> 36:34.303
and go from there?

36:34.358 --> 36:35.405
<i>Sounds good.</i>

36:35.655 --> 36:39.514
♪♪

36:39.561 --> 36:42.756
♪♪

36:43.099 --> 36:44.499
What the hell
is wrong with you?

36:44.764 --> 36:46.053
Nothing's wrong with me.

36:46.131 --> 36:47.835
I ordered you
to drop this thing.

36:47.883 --> 36:50.335
You didn't, so I figured out
a way to make you drop it.

36:50.384 --> 36:52.186
You think signing
Reform Corp. is going to

36:52.272 --> 36:54.006
make this go away,
you're out of your mind.

36:54.054 --> 36:55.233
And if you think that's true,

36:55.281 --> 36:56.695
you wouldn't be in my face
right now.

36:56.742 --> 36:59.139
Harvey, they are lining
their pockets on the backs

36:59.187 --> 37:01.142
of people who should have
gone free years ago,

37:01.221 --> 37:02.406
and you're letting them
get away with it.

37:02.453 --> 37:04.530
I'm their lawyer.
I'm not a prosecutor.

37:04.850 --> 37:06.843
What the fu... does
Alex Williams have on you, huh?

37:06.890 --> 37:08.053
Nobody has anything on me.

37:08.101 --> 37:09.242
Then why the hell
are you doing this?

37:09.289 --> 37:10.608
'Cause there's no way
it's for the money.

37:10.655 --> 37:12.664
- You don't understand.
- I'll tell you what I do understand.

37:12.711 --> 37:14.803
You owe him something,
and they have something on him,

37:14.830 --> 37:16.788
and if I can figure that out,
how long do you think

37:16.835 --> 37:18.584
it's gonna take before whatever
it is gets out anyway?

37:18.631 --> 37:19.677
You listen to me.

37:19.741 --> 37:21.083
If you ever valued the times

37:21.131 --> 37:23.412
that we've had each other's
backs, you'll have mine now,

37:23.460 --> 37:24.919
because I'm telling you,
I need it.

37:24.967 --> 37:26.341
Then tell me what's going on.

37:26.389 --> 37:28.513
I'm not going to do that,
because I can't trust you.

37:28.561 --> 37:30.810
But I'll tell you this: You lift
a finger to do something

37:30.858 --> 37:32.178
that even looks like
you're making

37:32.225 --> 37:33.763
another move on this case,

37:33.811 --> 37:35.771
I don't care if
you're calling Oscar Reyes

37:35.819 --> 37:37.826
to wish him a happy birthday,
you're fired.

37:37.874 --> 37:40.992
♪♪ <i>Tense music...</i>

37:41.040 --> 37:42.406
So why don't you take the night

37:42.461 --> 37:43.720
and decide if
you trust me enough

37:43.767 --> 37:45.204
to keep working here or not.

37:45.465 --> 37:49.100
♪♪

37:49.147 --> 37:52.930
♪♪

37:59.672 --> 38:01.156
Hey, hey.

38:01.302 --> 38:02.766
You here to check out
your new office?

38:02.813 --> 38:03.969
Because it's ready.

38:04.017 --> 38:05.922
Alex,
I'm staying at Pearson Hardman.

38:06.031 --> 38:08.374
- What?
- We had a deal.

38:08.422 --> 38:09.860
I know that,
but then I realized

38:09.908 --> 38:12.483
Jessica's family, and no title
is worth giving that up.

38:12.531 --> 38:13.851
I don't care
what you realized.

38:13.899 --> 38:16.132
I told Tommy Bratton
you'd sign on the dotted line.

38:16.180 --> 38:18.375
He pulled an offer to that
hotshot from skadden for me.

38:18.423 --> 38:19.999
I know this puts you
in a bad spot.

38:20.047 --> 38:21.843
Bad spot?
You stood in front of me,

38:21.891 --> 38:23.946
gave me your goddamn word,
and I banked on that,

38:24.000 --> 38:25.991
so I don't care what kind of
come-to-Jesus moment

38:26.039 --> 38:28.233
you think you had,
that shit is legally binding.

38:28.281 --> 38:30.757
If you want to try to
enforce that, go right ahead,

38:30.805 --> 38:32.143
but what does it say
to the world

38:32.191 --> 38:33.906
when a firm has to sue a lawyer

38:33.961 --> 38:35.413
just to get him to come there?

38:35.477 --> 38:37.273
What's it say when
I can't trust you anymore?

38:37.321 --> 38:40.477
Alex, you don't need me
to make partner.

38:41.221 --> 38:43.828
Maybe I don't,
but this is some bullshit.

38:43.938 --> 38:45.289
I'm not saying it's not.

38:45.337 --> 38:47.805
And I know right now,
my word means nothing,

38:47.895 --> 38:49.367
but I promise you,

38:49.502 --> 38:52.680
someday you're going to
need help with something,

38:53.360 --> 38:55.406
and no matter what it is,
I'll be there for you.

38:55.454 --> 38:56.640
I owe you one.

38:56.688 --> 38:57.874
And you can let it go or not,

38:57.922 --> 39:00.250
but I'm telling you, man to man,

39:00.539 --> 39:02.867
this is something I have to do.

39:02.993 --> 39:04.893
♪♪

39:05.051 --> 39:09.587
Okay, Harvey, I'll let it go,
but you do owe me one,

39:09.711 --> 39:12.031
and someday
I'm going to come calling.

39:12.152 --> 39:15.641
♪♪

39:15.688 --> 39:19.360
♪♪

39:27.844 --> 39:30.992
Harvey, I know
you want to help Alex,

39:31.438 --> 39:33.711
but if it means losing Mike,
then I have to ask,

39:33.813 --> 39:35.563
is it worth it?

39:36.090 --> 39:37.485
Mike went to prison for you.

39:37.571 --> 39:39.391
I know that, Donna.

39:42.508 --> 39:45.078
Harvey, what did Alex do?

39:45.631 --> 39:47.719
Why do you owe him?

39:54.293 --> 39:55.719
Alex.

39:56.150 --> 39:57.283
What are you doing here?

39:57.331 --> 39:58.594
I'm here to come clean to you.

39:58.648 --> 39:59.812
Does Harvey know you're here?

39:59.939 --> 40:02.000
No... in fact, he told me
not to talk to you at all,

40:02.055 --> 40:04.469
but you have a right
to know the truth, and...

40:04.797 --> 40:07.938
I'm tired of having this whole
thing hanging over my head.

40:08.625 --> 40:10.367
Come on in.

40:16.615 --> 40:20.133
After Alex told Bratton that
I wasn't coming, he was nothing.

40:20.297 --> 40:23.755
They gave him unwinnable cases
and worked him 90 hours a week

40:23.891 --> 40:25.812
until one day,
Bratton came to him

40:25.860 --> 40:27.586
and said there was a way back.

40:27.642 --> 40:28.821
All he had to do was take on

40:28.869 --> 40:30.422
Masterson construction
as a client.

40:30.489 --> 40:32.122
- Exactly.
- And he said yes.

40:32.265 --> 40:33.498
<i>Of course I said yes.</i>

40:33.546 --> 40:35.149
There were no red flags.

40:35.306 --> 40:38.797
The waiver that put inmates to
work was just smart business.

40:39.220 --> 40:40.711
On the surface,
everything was legit.

40:40.759 --> 40:42.478
So how'd you figure out
it wasn't?

40:42.531 --> 40:45.428
One day, I was at brunswick,
and a guard gave me a letter.

40:45.954 --> 40:47.782
It said an inmate had died
on the job site,

40:47.891 --> 40:49.413
and that it was being
covered up.

40:49.509 --> 40:52.517
Let me guess: You took it to
Pat Kreuger, Masterson's CEO,

40:52.571 --> 40:54.711
and he said that
he'd look into it.

40:54.774 --> 40:57.022
Two weeks later, that guard
was murdered by an inmate.

40:57.126 --> 40:58.243
<i>Holy shit.</i>

40:58.329 --> 40:59.391
And that's when he knew

40:59.439 --> 41:00.563
Masterson and reform corp.

41:00.611 --> 41:01.977
Had been colluding
from the start.

41:02.025 --> 41:03.188
So what did he do?

41:03.236 --> 41:04.586
He went to
his managing partner,

41:04.634 --> 41:07.593
and Tommy Bratton said it wasn't
collusion between two parties.

41:07.641 --> 41:09.336
It was collusion between
three parties.

41:09.384 --> 41:11.782
They tied all my bonuses
to all the key dates...

41:11.830 --> 41:13.672
- The waiver...
- The start of construction...

41:13.735 --> 41:15.173
- The guard's death...
- It looked like

41:15.220 --> 41:16.461
I orchestrated
the whole damn thing.

41:16.508 --> 41:17.663
So you covered up a murder?

41:17.711 --> 41:19.164
I had no proof of anything.

41:19.212 --> 41:21.267
I had a wife and daughter, and
it looked like I was in on it.

41:21.314 --> 41:24.196
Harvey, that's horrible,
but this isn't on you.

41:24.484 --> 41:26.451
Alex still could've made a call
anonymously.

41:26.532 --> 41:29.352
And so could you when
you found out Mike was a fraud.

41:29.650 --> 41:31.758
You didn't have to be a party
to a crime, but you were.

41:31.805 --> 41:33.094
That crime wasn't a murder.

41:33.142 --> 41:35.008
Did you hear me, Donna?
They had him.

41:35.056 --> 41:36.683
I had a wife and daughter,
and they set me up.

41:36.730 --> 41:38.844
What was I supposed to do?

41:39.867 --> 41:42.008
Mike, I hate these people.

41:42.094 --> 41:44.078
They deserve to go away
for what they did,

41:44.149 --> 41:46.196
and every morning when I woke up
and every night

41:46.244 --> 41:48.555
when I went to sleep,
I wanted to make that happen,

41:48.703 --> 41:52.211
but I didn't, for one reason:

41:52.367 --> 41:54.515
I didn't want my daughter
to grow up without a father,

41:54.579 --> 41:55.696
and if you pursue this,

41:55.744 --> 41:57.524
there's no way I don't get
caught up in it.

41:57.572 --> 41:58.792
- You don't know that.
- Yes, I do.

41:58.839 --> 42:00.508
When Bratton came after
our clients,

42:00.602 --> 42:03.720
Alex signed a declaration saying
he took full responsibility.

42:03.852 --> 42:05.945
Harvey, if you're asking Mike
to let this thing go...

42:06.015 --> 42:07.547
I don't know if I can do that.

42:07.642 --> 42:09.298
I'm not asking you
to let it go.

42:09.383 --> 42:11.727
I'm telling you what will happen
if you don't.

